other_tests.findings: Soft, nondistended abdomen; tenderness to palpation in RLQ at McBurney's point; voluntary guarding in RLQ; positive Rosving's sign; positive psoas sign; no rebound tenderness; no palpable masses.

Dilated appendix measuring up to 13 mm containing an appendicolith, fluid-filled with surrounding inflammatory stranding; no intraperitoneal free fluid or free air; normal liver, spleen, adrenals, pancreas, gallbladder; normal kidneys; normal aorta; no retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy.
